                            <comment id="12851024" author="tlipcon" created="Mon, 29 Mar 2010 17:59:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1, I love when error messages link to explanations about them. Very helpful to ops and users who aren&apos;t also developers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12851190" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 30 Mar 2010 01:06:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that makes the message coming from Sleeper much more helpful. I also updated the entry that the link refers to.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12851246" author="stack" created="Tue, 30 Mar 2010 04:40:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on commit.  The troubleshooting should probably become an xdoc that is checked in and rides along w/ the hbase version, but thats another project.  I thought the link in the message an auto-generated link but it looks like we have an explicit anchor in the wiki named &apos;9&apos; so should be fine as long as folks leave anchors as they are.  Good stuff J-D.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
